json.text: For 10 seasons our favorite group of friends never failed to make us, or each other laugh
Is everything okay?
Everything's fine
Welcome to Ms Mojo and today we're counting down our picks for the top 10 friends bloopers.
Are you saying that you don't wanna get with this?

00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,620
You see i don't say- *erupts into laughter*
For this list we're scouring the blooper reels of every season of this iconic sitcom
and are choosing the outtakes that crack us up the most
Did you tell her what we talked about?
Joey and Ross nap
Die Hard, still great, yeah
After sitting down to yet another screening of Joey's favorite movie "Die Hard" Joey and Ross accidentally fall asleep and end up cuddling
Joey considers it the best nap he's ever had
and keeps trying to convince or even trick Ross into napping with him again
"Come on, admit it, that was the best nap you ever had"
Silly premise? Yes, but watching it unfold still gets us giggling.
Come on!
Turns out that was the case for Matt Le Blanc and David Schwimmer too
Because the actors could barely get through the season 7 scene without breaking no matter how many times they shot it
it even came back later in the episode and again, resulted in gails of laughter
*screams*
*laughter*
Number 9: A little double take
" I cant believe Emma is still asleep"
"I know, what are we going to do?"
By the time 'Friends' had reached it's tenth season, the cast had grown very close.
Which means that on occasion, they'd poke fun at each other's on-set slip-ups
"I've got a plan. I've got a plan. I'm going to ram this platter really hard into your ribs
You're going to scream out, and that'll wake her up!"
As you can expect, two of the biggest players in this game were Matthew Perry and Matt Le Blanc
In a season ten episode, where the gang is trapped at Emma's first birthday party, because she won't wake up from her nap
Courtney Cox accidentally looks straight into the camera lens
"I can't believe- I just looked right at you I'm so sorry!"
Obviously the boys jump at the opportunity to mock her
"I can't believe Emma is still asleep! I know what are we going to do?"
What follows are a couple of ruined takes, and of course, some memorable bloopers.
Number eight: that WAS less!
"I did a terrible, stupid, stupid thing, okay? And I'm sorry, I wish I could take it back, but I cant."
The episode where Ross and Rachel break up is pretty somber.
To make sure things aren't too dark, the other friends keep the comedy flowing.
Monica and Phoebe are attempting to wax their legs, and it's more painful than they anticipated.
Their screams attract Chandler and Joey, who race into Monica's bedroom in an over-the-top fashion
"Hi, it's ok, it's ok!" " It's alright!"
An outake of this scene sees the boys asked to try again, as they've apparently been told their acting is too big
" We're alright." "Wait go back, go back." "That WAS less!"
Perry and Le Blanc poke fun at this piece of direction, entering the room as sedately as possible on the next take.
In this case, we're fine with the boys sabotaging yet another take for a great blooper.
"What's new?"
"Okay, okay, that's a print!"
Number seven: it tastes like feet!
"Raspberries, more lady fingers, then beef sauteed with peas and onions"
It's thanksgiving, and Rachel's been put in charge of dessert.
"Wha- What was the one right before bananas?"
"The beef? Yeah, that was weird to me too."
Unfortunately, due to some sticky magazine pages, she mistakenly messes up the recipe.
"Oh my god, she, she made half an English trifle, and half a shepherd's pie!"
Since Ross and Joey want to spare Rachel's feelings, and are dying to leave to hang out with some hot models, they decide not to tell her.
"We just wont tell her she messed up. Just let her serve the beef custard thing?"
But that means eating the meat pie/custardy dessert with a straight face.
"Does- Does it not taste good?"  "Let me try it." "Oh no no NO!"
All gone!
After Ross scarves his entire piece, which is tough enough in itself, David Schwimmer delivers his next line in such a way that he erupts in laughter.
"It's too much"
Matt Le Blanc doesn't even notice his co-star has broken and continues eating his pie but ultimately he's unable to fight off the giggles.
" I like it"
(Audience laughter)
Number six: Rachel and the Monkey.
"And I will see you tomorrow!"
"That's right, and you're gonna spend tomorrow at Aunt Rachel's, aren't you, huh?"
Early in the show's run, Ross gets a Capuchin monkey as a pet and names it Marcell, much to the cast's dismay.
"Now you guys worked.. with animals alot
You did some work early on.. with a monkey?"
"That damn monkey."
They say never work with children, or animals.
And here's why...
Apparently the monkey, who was actually named Katie,
sometimes had trouble following instructions, and disrupted takes.
"Oh look, oh look! There's- okay."
In a Marcel-centric season one episode, Rachel is baby-sitting Marcel,
and trying to explain a soap opera to him.
But as you can see in the blooper,
Jennifer Aniston has a difficult time predicting what Katie is going to do.
This makes for a hilarious and, quite frankly, adorable outtake,
that neither we, nor Jennifer, will likely  ever forget.
*Jennifer struggles*
Number Five: Phoebe Laughs.
Rachel: "Lisa's laugh though. It's so infectious,
it's one of those things, just forget about it.
Once it starts, it's all gone.
Nothing sends the 'Friends' cast quite into fits of glee quite like Lisa Kudrow's infectious laugh.
*guess what, Lisa Kudrow laughs*
In a Season Six episode, after Phoebe and Rachel's apartment burns down,
The girls are arguing over who has to live with Monica and her strict house rules,
and who gets to have fun at Joey's.

But once Kudrow starts laughing, 
for no apparent reason,
It's hard for her to stop.
